article.headline: Rider 68, Dartmouth 64
article.story: HILO, Hawaii (AP) -- Rider got off to a slow start Sunday, but came on strong in the second half to beat Dartmouth 68-64 at the round-robin Hilo Shootout. Dartmouth (0-4) took a 13-0 lead before Jerry Johnson hit a pair of free throws to get Rider (3-1) on the board. The Broncs missed their first 10 shots from the field before Robert Taylor hit a jumper with 13:01 left in the first half. Dartmouth led 34-22 at halftime and was up 40-29 in the second half when Rider went on a 10-0 run to pull to with one point. Dartmouth made two free throws only to have Laurence Young's 3-pointer tie the score. Johnson led Rider with 24 points, Young had 17 and Armel Minyem added 10. Leon Pattmen was high for Dartmouth with 15 points. Teammates Scott Klingbeil and Michael Lang had 12 apiece.
